agentGeneralMgmt.name: agentGeneralMgmt
agentGeneralMgmt.description: The structure of general management information for enterprise.

Ipv6Address.name: Ipv6Address
Ipv6Address.description: This data type is used to model IPv6 addresses. This is a binary string of 16 octets in network byte-order.

agentMgmtProtocolCapability.name: agentMgmtProtocolCapability
agentMgmtProtocolCapability.description: The network management protocol(s) supported by this agent.

agentMibCapabilityTable.name: agentMibCapabilityTable
agentMibCapabilityTable.description: A list of MIB capability entries supported by this agent.

agentMibCapabilityEntry.name: agentMibCapabilityEntry
agentMibCapabilityEntry.description: A MIB capability entry containing objects that describe a particular MIB supported by this agent.

agentMibCapabilityIndex.name: agentMibCapabilityIndex
agentMibCapabilityIndex.description: A list of Agent MIB Capability Description entries.

agentMibCapabilityDescr.name: agentMibCapabilityDescr
agentMibCapabilityDescr.description: The name of the MIB supported by the agent.

agentMibCapabilityVersion.name: agentMibCapabilityVersion
agentMibCapabilityVersion.description: The version of the MIB specified in this entry.

agentMibCapabilityType.name: agentMibCapabilityType
agentMibCapabilityType.description: The type of MIB specified in this entry.

agentStatusConsoleInUse.name: agentStatusConsoleInUse
agentStatusConsoleInUse.description: This indicates whether the console is currently in use.

agentStatusSaveCfg.name: agentStatusSaveCfg
agentStatusSaveCfg.description: This indicates the status of the device configuration. other (1) - This entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are determined by each of the following values. proceeding (2) - The device configuration is currently being saved into NV-RAM. completed (3) - All of the device configuration parameters have been saved into NV-RAM. failed (4) - The process to save the device configuration has failed.

agentStatusFileTransfer.name: agentStatusFileTransfer
agentStatusFileTransfer.description: The status of the firmware download control. If the value is stated as 'other', the firmware has not been updated since the device was started.

agentCPUutilizationIn5sec.name: agentCPUutilizationIn5sec
agentCPUutilizationIn5sec.description: The time scale is set at 5 second intervals. The value will be between 0% (idle) and 100% (very busy).

agentCPUutilizationIn1min.name: agentCPUutilizationIn1min
agentCPUutilizationIn1min.description: The time scale is set at 1 minute intervals. The value will be between 0% (idle) and 100% (very busy).

agentCPUutilizationIn5min.name: agentCPUutilizationIn5min
agentCPUutilizationIn5min.description: The time scale is set at 5 minute intervals. The value will be between 0% (idle) and 100% (very busy).

agentPORTutilizationTable.name: agentPORTutilizationTable
agentPORTutilizationTable.description: This table specifies the current utilization of a specified port.

agentPORTutilizationEntry.name: agentPORTutilizationEntry
agentPORTutilizationEntry.description: A list of information regarding the port utilization function.

agentPORTutilizationProtIndex.name: agentPORTutilizationProtIndex
agentPORTutilizationProtIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.

agentPORTutilizationTX.name: agentPORTutilizationTX
agentPORTutilizationTX.description: The current rate of transmitted frames on the specified port.

agentPORTutilizationRX.name: agentPORTutilizationRX
agentPORTutilizationRX.description: The current rate of received frames on the specified port.

agentPORTutilizationUtil.name: agentPORTutilizationUtil
agentPORTutilizationUtil.description: The current percentages regarding port statistics.

agentDRAMutilizationEntry.name: agentDRAMutilizationEntry
agentDRAMutilizationEntry.description: A list of information about DRAM memory.

agentDRAMutilizationUnitID.name: agentDRAMutilizationUnitID
agentDRAMutilizationUnitID.description: Specifies the unit ID. If the ID equals zero, it means the current device.

agentDRAMutilizationTotalDRAM.name: agentDRAMutilizationTotalDRAM
agentDRAMutilizationTotalDRAM.description: The size of total DRAM memory.

agentDRAMutilizationUsedDRAM.name: agentDRAMutilizationUsedDRAM
agentDRAMutilizationUsedDRAM.description: The size of used DRAM memory.

agentDRAMutilization.name: agentDRAMutilization
agentDRAMutilization.description: The percentage of used DRAM memory of the total DRAM memory available. The value will be between 0% (idle) and 100% (very busy).

agentFLASHutilizationUnitID.name: agentFLASHutilizationUnitID
agentFLASHutilizationUnitID.description: Specifies the unit ID. If the ID equals zero, it means the current device.

agentFLASHutilizationTotalFLASH.name: agentFLASHutilizationTotalFLASH
agentFLASHutilizationTotalFLASH.description: The total size of flash memory.

agentFLASHutilizationUsedFLASH.name: agentFLASHutilizationUsedFLASH
agentFLASHutilizationUsedFLASH.description: The size of the used flash memory.

agentFLASHutilization.name: agentFLASHutilization
agentFLASHutilization.description: The percentage of used flash memory in total flash memory. The value will be between 0% (idle) and 100% (very busy).

agentSerialNumber.name: agentSerialNumber
agentSerialNumber.description: A text string containing the serial number of this device.

agentFirmwareType.name: agentFirmwareType
agentFirmwareType.description: A text string containing the firmware type.

agentBscSwFileTable.name: agentBscSwFileTable
agentBscSwFileTable.description: A list of MIB Basic Config entry support files updated by this agent.

agentBscSwFileEntry.name: agentBscSwFileEntry
agentBscSwFileEntry.description: A basic configuration entry containing the objects that describe a particular MIB supported by this agent.

agentBscSwFileIndex.name: agentBscSwFileIndex
agentBscSwFileIndex.description: The table index for the file entry

agentBscSwFileDscr.name: agentBscSwFileDscr
agentBscSwFileDscr.description: The description of the software file purpose in this entry. Note: For systems that do not support a change to this object, setting a value for this object will cause the system to return bad-value error messages.

agentBscSwFileAddr.name: agentBscSwFileAddr
agentBscSwFileAddr.description: The IP address where the file that needs to be downloaded is located, or the IP address where the file will be uploaded to.

agentBscSwFileTransferType.name: agentBscSwFileTransferType
agentBscSwFileTransferType.description: The channel through which the file will be downloaded or uploaded. Note: For systems that do not support all channels, setting a value to the unsupported channel will cause the system to return bad-value error messages.

agentBscSwFile.name: agentBscSwFile
agentBscSwFile.description: The name of the file to be downloaded from, or uploaded to, the TFTP server.

agentBscSwFileLocateId.name: agentBscSwFileLocateId
agentBscSwFileLocateId.description: This object describes the type of file. runtime-code (1), log-file (2), cfg-file (3) Note: For systems that do not support changes to this object, setting a value for this object will cause the system to return bad-value error messages.

agentBscSwFileLoadType.name: agentBscSwFileLoadType
agentBscSwFileLoadType.description: This object provides the user with a choice of uploading or downloading the selected file. Note: For systems that do not support a change to this object, setting a value for this object will cause the system to return bad-value error messages.

agentBscSwFileCtrl.name: agentBscSwFileCtrl
agentBscSwFileCtrl.description: This object gives the user the option of downloading runtime software. This setting will take effect when the system restarts. See Note (1) below Note: For systems that do not support changes to this object, setting a value to this object will cause the system to return bad-value error messages. start - Activate firmware. delete (4) - Delete the firmware by indicated firmware ID. config-as-bootup (5) - Configured as bootup firmware by the indicated firmware(ID). apply (6) - Apply the configuration to be the active configuration by the indicated config ID.

agentBscSwFileBIncrement.name: agentBscSwFileBIncrement
agentBscSwFileBIncrement.description: This object indicates whether the previous configuration will remain valid or not after downloading the configuration file. True: Keep valid False: Erase.

agentBscSwFileCtrlID.name: agentBscSwFileCtrlID
agentBscSwFileCtrlID.description: The section ID of the firmware image or configuration file. A value of 0 indicates the boot-up firmware image or configuration file.

agentBscSwFileCtrlUnitID.name: agentBscSwFileCtrlUnitID
agentBscSwFileCtrlUnitID.description: Specifies which unit of the switch stack the firmware image will be downloaded from. One or more units can be set in this list. Each bit from the left to the right represents the switch from unit ID 1 to unit ID 12. A null entry in this field denotes all switches in the switch stack.

agentBscSwFileIPv6Addr.name: agentBscSwFileIPv6Addr
agentBscSwFileIPv6Addr.description: The IPv6 address where the file will be downloaded from or uploaded to.

agentBscSwFileBootUpImage.name: agentBscSwFileBootUpImage
agentBscSwFileBootUpImage.description: The result of the download will depend on whether the boot_up option is specified. Case 1: In the case where the master unit provides the file system and the slave unit does not provide the file system, when boot_up is specified, the file will be downloaded to the boot_up image on the slave. If boot_up is not specified, then the file will not be downloaded to this slave unit. Case 2: In the case where the master unit does not provide the file system and the slave unit provides the file system, when boot_up is specified, the file will be downloaded to the boot_up image on the slave unit. If boot_up is not specified, the file will not be downloaded to this slave unit. Case 3: In the case where the master unit and the slave unit both support or do not support the file system, the file will be downloaded to the specified file on the slave unit. If boot_up is specified, the downloaded file will be assigned as the boot_up image. True: boot_up option is specified. False: boot_up option is not specified.

agentBscSwFileForceAgree.name: agentBscSwFileForceAgree
agentBscSwFileForceAgree.description: When the force_agree option is specified, the reboot command will be executed immediately, without any further confirmation from the user. True: force_agree option is specified. False: force_agree option is not specified.

agentBscSwFileInterfaceName.name: agentBscSwFileInterfaceName
agentBscSwFileInterfaceName.description: This node is used to specify the interface name when the agentBscSwFileIPv6Addr is the link local address.

agentBscSwFileServerDomainName.name: agentBscSwFileServerDomainName
agentBscSwFileServerDomainName.description: This object indicates the domain name of the TFTP server.

agentFileTransfer.name: agentFileTransfer
agentFileTransfer.description: This object will execute the download or upload action. If start (2) is chosen, it will begin to download/upload and no reset will follow. If start-and-reset (3) is chosen, then the reset will be activated after completing the download or upload. No action if noaction (4) is chosen. Note: Because these functions will be limited by the support for the system in question, some of the selected items will be invalid. When the user selects an invalid entry, the system will respond with a bad-value status.

agentSystemReset.name: agentSystemReset
agentSystemReset.description: This object indicates the agent system reset state. Setting this object to no-reset (4) has no effect. Setting this object to cold-start (2) or warm-start (3) will reset the agent. The agent always returns to no-reset (4) when this object is read. This object is replaced by 'agentReset'.

agentRs232PortConfig.name: agentRs232PortConfig
agentRs232PortConfig.description: This object indicates the RS-232C mode once the device has restarted.

agentOutOfBandBaudRateConfig.name: agentOutOfBandBaudRateConfig
agentOutOfBandBaudRateConfig.description: This object allows the user to specify an out-of-band baud rate, which will take effect upon system restart. Note: Because these functions will be limited by the support for the system in question, some of the selected items will be invalid. When the user selects an invalid entry, the system will respond with a bad-value error message.

agentSaveCfg.name: agentSaveCfg
agentSaveCfg.description: This object indicates the type of save command to be executed, when saving to NV-RAM. other (1) - None of the following. cfg-id1 (2) - Save configuration ID1. cfg-id2 (3)- Save configuration ID2. log (4) - Save log. all (5) - Save both (active configuration and log).

swMultiImageInfoEntry.name: swMultiImageInfoEntry
swMultiImageInfoEntry.description: A list of information about multiple image management.

swMultiImageInfoID.name: swMultiImageInfoID
swMultiImageInfoID.description: The stacking section ID of the firmware image. The stacking section ID = 256 * Unit ID + Image File ID.

swMultiImageFrom.name: swMultiImageFrom
swMultiImageFrom.description: The recorded IP address of the TFTP server

swMultiImageSendUser.name: swMultiImageSendUser
swMultiImageSendUser.description: The record of the user who downloaded the firmware.

swMultiImageFileName.name: swMultiImageFileName
swMultiImageFileName.description: When the system is set to boot from SD card, this object will display the recorded path name of the boot firmware file.

swMultiCfgInfoEntry.name: swMultiCfgInfoEntry
swMultiCfgInfoEntry.description: A list of information about multiple configuration files.

swMultiCfgInfoID.name: swMultiCfgInfoID
swMultiCfgInfoID.description: The section ID of the configuration files.

swMultiCfgSize.name: swMultiCfgSize
swMultiCfgSize.description: The recorded downloaded configuration size (in bytes).

swMultiCFgUpdateTime.name: swMultiCFgUpdateTime
swMultiCFgUpdateTime.description: The recorded configuration update time displayed in string format, i.e. yyyy/mon/dd hh:mm:ss.

swMultiCfgFrom.name: swMultiCfgFrom
swMultiCfgFrom.description: The recorded IP address of the TFTP server.

swMultiCfgSendUser.name: swMultiCfgSendUser
swMultiCfgSendUser.description: The record of the user who downloaded the configuration file

swMultiCfgFileName.name: swMultiCfgFileName
swMultiCfgFileName.description: When the system is set to boot from SD card, this object displays the recorded path name of the boot configuration file.

swMultiCfgCurrentUsed.name: swMultiCfgCurrentUsed
swMultiCfgCurrentUsed.description: The indicated configuration file ID of the system currently in use.

swMultiCfgBootUp.name: swMultiCfgBootUp
swMultiCfgBootUp.description: This object indicates the configuration file ID which will take effect upon the next reboot.

swMultiCfgCtrlEntry.name: swMultiCfgCtrlEntry
swMultiCfgCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about multiple configuration management.

swMultiCfgCtrlID.name: swMultiCfgCtrlID
swMultiCfgCtrlID.description: The section ID of the configuration file.

swMultiCfgAction.name: swMultiCfgAction
swMultiCfgAction.description: save: Save configuration to active configuration ID when the parameter is omitted. active: Set any valid configuration as the active configuration. delete: Removes the configuration from the flash memory. This configuration cannot be the active or current configuration file. apply: Loads the indicated configuration file and applies it to the system. config-as-bootup-cfg: Configured as the boot-up configuration by the indicated configuration(ID).

systemSeverityTrapControl.name: systemSeverityTrapControl
systemSeverityTrapControl.description: Indicates the level of trap severity control. The system has a severity level control and each trap should have a severity control set. When trap events occur and its severity is higher than the system severity control level, the trap works as defined. If the event severity is lower than the system severity control level, the event is ignored as if it did not occur.

systemSeverityLogControl.name: systemSeverityLogControl
systemSeverityLogControl.description: Indicates the level of trap severity control. The system has a severity level control and each trap should have a severity control set. When trap events occur and its severity is higher than the system severity control level, the trap works as defined. If the event severity is lower than the system severity control level, the event is ignored as if it did not occur.

agentTrustedHostTable.name: agentTrustedHostTable
agentTrustedHostTable.description: This table contains the trusted host information.

agentTrustedHostEntry.name: agentTrustedHostEntry
agentTrustedHostEntry.description: A list of information about the trusted hosts.

agentTrustedHostIndex.name: agentTrustedHostIndex
agentTrustedHostIndex.description: The index of the trusted host entry.

agentTrustedHostIPAddress.name: agentTrustedHostIPAddress
agentTrustedHostIPAddress.description: Specifies the IP address of the trusted host.

agentTrustedHostRowStatus.name: agentTrustedHostRowStatus
agentTrustedHostRowStatus.description: Indicates the status of this entry. When creating a trusted host entry, the IP address should also be set.

agentTrustedHostIPSubnetMask.name: agentTrustedHostIPSubnetMask
agentTrustedHostIPSubnetMask.description: Specifies the IP subnet mask of the trusted host.

agentTrustedHostForSNMP.name: agentTrustedHostForSNMP
agentTrustedHostForSNMP.description: Specifies the trusted host for SNMP.

agentTrustedHostForTELNET.name: agentTrustedHostForTELNET
agentTrustedHostForTELNET.description: Specifies the trusted host for Telnet.

agentTrustedHostForSSH.name: agentTrustedHostForSSH
agentTrustedHostForSSH.description: Specifies the trusted host for SSH.

agentTrustedHostForHTTP.name: agentTrustedHostForHTTP
agentTrustedHostForHTTP.description: Specifies the trusted host for HTTP.

agentTrustedHostForHTTPS.name: agentTrustedHostForHTTPS
agentTrustedHostForHTTPS.description: Specifies the trusted host for HTTPS.

agentTrustedHostForPING.name: agentTrustedHostForPING
agentTrustedHostForPING.description: Specifies the trusted host for PING.

agentTrustedHostAddrType.name: agentTrustedHostAddrType
agentTrustedHostAddrType.description: The type of trusted host address as specified by the 'agentTrustedHostAddr' object.

agentTrustedHostAddr.name: agentTrustedHostAddr
agentTrustedHostAddr.description: Specifies the IP address of the trusted host.

agentTrustedHostIPv6PrefixLen.name: agentTrustedHostIPv6PrefixLen
agentTrustedHostIPv6PrefixLen.description: Specifies the IPv6 prefix length of the IPv6 trusted host.

agentTrustedHostDelAllState.name: agentTrustedHostDelAllState
agentTrustedHostDelAllState.description: Used to delete all trusted host entries.

agentFDBClearAllState.name: agentFDBClearAllState
agentFDBClearAllState.description: Used to clear all FDB entries.

agentFDBClearByPortTable.name: agentFDBClearByPortTable
agentFDBClearByPortTable.description: Used to clear FDB entries by port.

agentFDBClearByPortEntry.name: agentFDBClearByPortEntry
agentFDBClearByPortEntry.description: This is an entry of the agentFDBClearByPortTable.

agentFDBClearPortIndex.name: agentFDBClearPortIndex
agentFDBClearPortIndex.description: This object indicates the port number.

agentFDBClearByPortAction.name: agentFDBClearByPortAction
agentFDBClearByPortAction.description: This object indicates whether to clear FDB or not.

agentFDBClearByVlanTable.name: agentFDBClearByVlanTable
agentFDBClearByVlanTable.description: Used to clear FDB entries by port.

agentFDBClearByVlanEntry.name: agentFDBClearByVlanEntry
agentFDBClearByVlanEntry.description: This is an entry of agentFDBClearByPortTable.

agentFDBClearByVlanAction.name: agentFDBClearByVlanAction
agentFDBClearByVlanAction.description: This object indicates whether to clear the FDB or not.

agentFDBSecurityTable.name: agentFDBSecurityTable
agentFDBSecurityTable.description: Used to display the FDB entries that have been created by the security module.

agentFDBSecurityEntry.name: agentFDBSecurityEntry
agentFDBSecurityEntry.description: This is an entry of agentFDBSecurityTable.

agentFDBMacAddress.name: agentFDBMacAddress
agentFDBMacAddress.description: This object indicates the MAC address.

agentFDBPort.name: agentFDBPort
agentFDBPort.description: This object indicates the port number.

agentFDBType.name: agentFDBType
agentFDBType.description: This object indicates the MAC address type.

agentFDBStatus.name: agentFDBStatus
agentFDBStatus.description: This object indicates the MAC address's forwarding status.

agentFDBSecurityModule.name: agentFDBSecurityModule
agentFDBSecurityModule.description: This object is used to indicate which security module created the current MAC address. dot1x: 802.1X. wac: Web-based Access Control. jwac: Web-Based Access Control extension for Japan. port-security: Port Security. mac-based-access-control: MAC-based Access Control. compound-authentication: Compound Authentication.

agentARPClearAllState.name: agentARPClearAllState
agentARPClearAllState.description: Used to clear all ARP entries.

agentGratuitousARPSendIpifStatusUpState.name: agentGratuitousARPSendIpifStatusUpState
agentGratuitousARPSendIpifStatusUpState.description: This is used to enable/disable sending of gratuitous ARP request packets while the IPIF interface comes up. This is used to automatically announce the interface's IP address to other nodes. By default, the state is enabled, and only one ARP packet will be broadcast.

agentGratuitousARPSendDupIpDetectedState.name: agentGratuitousARPSendDupIpDetectedState
agentGratuitousARPSendDupIpDetectedState.description: This is used to enable/disable the sending of gratuitous ARP request packets while a duplicate IP is detected. By default, the state is enabled. The duplicate IP detected state indicates that the system has received an ARP request packet that was sent by an IP address that matches the system's own IP address. In this case, the system knows that somebody out there is using an IP address that is in conflict with the system. In order to reclaim the correct host of this IP address, the system can send out the gratuitous ARP request packet for this duplicate IP address.

agentGratuitousARPLearningState.name: agentGratuitousARPLearningState
agentGratuitousARPLearningState.description: This is used to enable/disable learning of an ARP entry in the ARP cache based on the received gratuitous ARP packet. If the switch receives a gratuitous ARP request/reply packet and the sender's IP address is in its ARP table, it should update the ARP entry. By default, the state is disabled.

agentGratuitousARPEntry.name: agentGratuitousARPEntry
agentGratuitousARPEntry.description: A list of information from the Gratuitous ARP Table.

agentGratuitousARPInterfaceName.name: agentGratuitousARPInterfaceName
agentGratuitousARPInterfaceName.description: The name of the IP interface.

agentGratuitousARPPeriodicalSendInterval.name: agentGratuitousARPPeriodicalSendInterval
agentGratuitousARPPeriodicalSendInterval.description: This is used to configure the interval for the periodic sending of gratuitous ARP request packets. 0 means do not send gratuitous ARP request packets periodically.

agentGratuitousARPTrapState.name: agentGratuitousARPTrapState
agentGratuitousARPTrapState.description: This indicates the state of the gratuitous ARP trap. The switch can trap the IP conflict events to inform the administrator. By default, the trap is disabled.

agentGratuitousARPLogState.name: agentGratuitousARPLogState
agentGratuitousARPLogState.description: This indicates the state of the gratuitous Log trap. The switch can log the IP conflict events to inform the administrator. By default, the event log is enabled.

agentARPTotalARPEntries.name: agentARPTotalARPEntries
agentARPTotalARPEntries.description: Used to display the total number of ARP entries.

agentARPRetryTimes.name: agentARPRetryTimes
agentARPRetryTimes.description: This indicates the retry times of the ARP request.

swMultiImageCtrlEntry.name: swMultiImageCtrlEntry
swMultiImageCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about multiple image management.

swMultiImageCtrlID.name: swMultiImageCtrlID
swMultiImageCtrlID.description: The stacking section ID of the firmware image. The stacking section ID = 256 * Unit ID + Image File ID.

swMultiImageCtrlAction.name: swMultiImageCtrlAction
swMultiImageCtrlAction.description: This object indicates the running status of the image which is specified by swMultiImageCtrlID and swMultiImageCtrlUnitID. config-as-bootup-fw (1) - Configured as the bootup firmware by the indicated firmware(ID). delete (2) - Delete the firmware by indicated firmware ID. none (3) - No action.

agentOutOfBandDataBits.name: agentOutOfBandDataBits
agentOutOfBandDataBits.description: This object indicates the out-of-band data bits.

agentOutOfBandParityBits.name: agentOutOfBandParityBits
agentOutOfBandParityBits.description: This object indicates the out-of-band parity bits.

agentOutOfBandStopBits.name: agentOutOfBandStopBits
agentOutOfBandStopBits.description: This object indicates the out-of-band stop bits.

agentOutOfBandAutoLogoutConfig.name: agentOutOfBandAutoLogoutConfig
agentOutOfBandAutoLogoutConfig.description: This object allows the user to specify an out-of-band auto logout time.

agentBscFileSystemTable.name: agentBscFileSystemTable
agentBscFileSystemTable.description: A list of MIB File System Basic Configuration entries supported by the file update of this agent.

agentBscFileSystemEntry.name: agentBscFileSystemEntry
agentBscFileSystemEntry.description: A File System basic configuration entry that contains objects describing a particular MIB supported by this agent.

agentBscFileSystemIndex.name: agentBscFileSystemIndex
agentBscFileSystemIndex.description: The table index for the file entry. This object describes the file type. runtime-code (1), log-file (2), cfg-file (3), attack-log-file (7)

agentBscFileSystemDscr.name: agentBscFileSystemDscr
agentBscFileSystemDscr.description: The description of the software file purpose in this entry.

agentBscFileSystemServerAddr.name: agentBscFileSystemServerAddr
agentBscFileSystemServerAddr.description: The IP address where the file to be downloaded is located, or the IP address where the file will be uploaded to.

agentBscFileSystemServerIPv6Addr.name: agentBscFileSystemServerIPv6Addr
agentBscFileSystemServerIPv6Addr.description: The IPv6 address where the file is to be downloaded from or uploaded to.

agentBscFileSystemServerFileName.name: agentBscFileSystemServerFileName
agentBscFileSystemServerFileName.description: The name of the file to be downloaded from or uploaded to the TFTP server. If agentBscFileSystemDeviceFileName is not set, the switch will default to using the bootup file as the runtime image for the switch.

agentBscFileSystemDeviceDriverID.name: agentBscFileSystemDeviceDriverID
agentBscFileSystemDeviceDriverID.description: Specifies the drive of the device that the firmware to be uploaded/downloaded is located. If none (1) is specified, the switch will default to the current drive.

agentBscFileSystemDeviceFileName.name: agentBscFileSystemDeviceFileName
agentBscFileSystemDeviceFileName.description: The name of the file to be downloaded to the device, or uploaded from the device. When downloading or uploading, the agentBscFileSystemServerFileName object must also be set.

agentBscFileSystemLoadType.name: agentBscFileSystemLoadType
agentBscFileSystemLoadType.description: This object allows the user to select a download or upload function for the file. Note: For systems that do not support changes to this object, setting a value for this object will cause the system to return a bad-value error message.

agentBscFileSystemCtrlUnitID.name: agentBscFileSystemCtrlUnitID
agentBscFileSystemCtrlUnitID.description: Specifies which unit of the switch stack the firmware image or configuration file should be downloaded from. One or more units can be set in this list. Each bit from left to right represents the switch from unit ID 1 to unit ID 12. If this list is set to null it represents all stack switches.

agentBscFileSystemBootUpImage.name: agentBscFileSystemBootUpImage
agentBscFileSystemBootUpImage.description: The result of the download will depend on whether the boot_up option has been specified. Case 1: In the case of the master unit providing the file system and the slave unit not providing the file system, when the boot_up parameter is specified, then the file will be downloaded to the boot_up image on the slave. If the boot_up parameter is not specified, then the file will not be downloaded to this slave unit. Case 2: In the case of the master unit not providing the file system and the slave unit providing the file system, when the boot_up parameter is specified, then the file will be downloaded to the boot_up image on the slave unit. If boot_up is not specified, then the file will not be downloaded to this slave unit. Case 3: In the case of the master unit and the slave unit both supporting or not supporting the file system, the file will be downloaded to the specified file on the slave unit. If boot_up is specified, the downloaded file will be assigned as the boot_up image. True: boot_up option is specified. False: boot_up option is not specified..

agentBscFileSystemForceAgree.name: agentBscFileSystemForceAgree
agentBscFileSystemForceAgree.description: When the force_agree option is specified, the reboot command will be executed immediately without any further confirmation from the user. True: force_agree option is specified. False: force_agree option is not specified..

agentBscFileSystemCtrl.name: agentBscFileSystemCtrl
agentBscFileSystemCtrl.description: This object allows the user to download runtime software. The settings will take effect when the system restarts. See Note (1) below Note 1: For systems which do not support value changes to this object, setting these values will cause the system to return a bad-value error message start (3) - activate firmware.

agentBscFileSystemInterfaceName.name: agentBscFileSystemInterfaceName
agentBscFileSystemInterfaceName.description: This node is used to specify the interface name when agentBscFileSystemServerIPv6Addr is the local link address.

agentBscFileSystemServerDomainName.name: agentBscFileSystemServerDomainName
agentBscFileSystemServerDomainName.description: This object indicates the domain name of the TFTP server.

agentBscFileSystemIncrement.name: agentBscFileSystemIncrement
agentBscFileSystemIncrement.description: If increment is specified, then the existing configuration will not be cleared before applying of the new configuration. If it is not specified, then the existing configuration will be cleared before applying of the new configuration. True : keep valid False : erase.

agentBscFileSystemSaveConfigDriverID.name: agentBscFileSystemSaveConfigDriverID
agentBscFileSystemSaveConfigDriverID.description: The drive on the device that the configuration file is will be saved to. If none (1) is specified, the switch places the file on the current drive by default.

agentBscFileSystemSaveConfigFileName.name: agentBscFileSystemSaveConfigFileName

agentReset.name: agentReset
agentReset.description: Used to reset all switch parameters. none (1): No action. This is the default value of this object. config (2): All parameters are reset to default settings. The device will neither save nor reboot. system (3): All parameters are reset to default settings. The switch will then do a factory reset, save, and reboot. reset (4) : All parameters will be reset to default settings except for the IP address, user account, and history log. The device will neither save nor reboot. system-exclude-vlan(5) : All parameters are reset to default settings except for VLAN. The switch will then save its settings and reboot. system-exclude-ip(6) : All parameters are reset to default settings except IP address. The switch will then save its settings and reboot. system-exclude-vlan-ip(7): All parameters are reset to default settings except VLAN and IP address. The switch will then save its settings and reboot.
